 Job Description 
 SRI International's Artificial Intelligence Center (AIC) is seeking researchers in the area of natural language processing (NLP) to work in the Advanced Analytics group in San Diego, California. 
 
We are seeking innovators to develop cutting-edge artificial intelligence solutions for a broad range of problems involving human language. Past and present research in the group spans a wide range of use cases, including: automated understanding of the biological or chemistry literature; extraction from textual procedures; automatic induction of linguistic structure and semantics from text corpora; and models of idea propagation and influence in online communities. Successful applicants will work as part of a team to address challenging problems for commercial and government clients. There are multiple positions available requiring experience in any or all of the following areas: computational linguistics, empirical natural language processing, text mining, computational socio-linguistics, and multi-source data processing (images, audio, video, text, etc.). 
 Qualifications 
 Candidates for the position should have: 
 An advanced degree (Masterâ€™s required, Ph.D. preferred) in Computer Science or a related field Experience in applying machine learning to real-world problems involving natural language An ability to use, adapt, and extend approaches described in the scientific literature relevant to NLP Strong computational and mathematical skills, with demonstrated programming experience Excellent oral and written communication skills The ability to work effectively with diverse groups of people 
Though the Advanced Analytics group is located in SRIâ€™s San Diego office, the option exists to work in SRIâ€™s headquarters in Menlo Park, California. 
